COMMON TERMS & CONDITIONS
1. All potential bidders must fill up the registration form or register before 10:00 AM on the day of Auction.
2. Upon submission of the valid Power of Attorney or Authorization Letter, a bidder representing the interested buyers or group of buyers shall be required to fill in and sign
a prescribed Proxy Form (BNBL will issue proxy form during registration)
3. A registration fees of Nu.300 (Non Refundable) with an earnest money of Nu.25,000.00 to be deposited in cash /BNBL cheque/online payment not later than 10.00 AM
on the day of auction.
4. Earnest money of unsuccessful bidders shall be refunded.
5. The bidder with the highest bid shall be considered as successful bidder and no bidder shall be allowed to retract their bid(s). All sales are final and binding.
6. For every successful bid, the bidder is required to make payment of 25% of the bid amount by CASH/BNBL cheque immediately after the fall of hammer. The balance is
to be paid on or before the expiry of *TEN WORKING DAYS* from the date of Auction and take delivery of the property.
7. All applicable renewal fee/ownership transfer tax and charges payable to the relevant agency or authority shall be borne by the successful bidder.
8. The successful bidder will not be entitled to the property(ies) purchased until the total bid amount have been fully paid and adjusted. In the event that the bidder fails to
pay the full bid amount for the property within the prescribed time, deposits/payment made shall be forfeited.
9. The bidder shall be deemed to have physically inspected the property (*AS IS WHERE IS BASIS*) to their full satisfaction before making their bid(s). Any issues/
discrepancies arising after the property(ies) have been handed over to the successful bidder by the bank, the bank shall not be held liable.
10. The Bank may at any time withdraw the property(ies) from the auction before or on the auction date at its own discretion.